Three years ago, a gunman attacked the Tree of Life Synagogue in Pittsburgh, killing 11 people and injuring others. This was the deadliest act of antisemitism in U.S. history. The article highlights the resilience and strength of the community in the face of hate, with first responders, teenagers, and artists coming together to support each other. It emphasizes the importance of standing up against hate and recognizing our shared humanity. The administration has taken steps to address domestic terrorism, strengthen efforts against hate crimes, and protect houses of worship. As the anniversary approaches, the article calls for remembering the lives lost and creating a future worthy of their memories.